Question 2

You can also embed plots, for example:

mat_ones <- function(n){
  
  m <- matrix(1,ncol=n,nrow=n)
  m[upper.tri(m)] <- 0
  return(apply(m, 2, rev))
  
}

mat_ones(10)

Question 3

cumsum.v <- function(x){
  cumsum.vector <- rep(0,length(x))
  
  for (i in x){
    cumsum <- sum(x[c(1:i)])
    cumsum.vector[i] <- cumsum
  }
  return(cumsum.vector)
}

cumsum.v(c(1:5))
## [1]  1  3  6 10 15

Question 7

set.seed(2864)
x <- rnorm(20,1,1)
y <- rnorm(20,1.1,1.1)

x_bar <- mean(x)
y_bar <- mean(y)

sx <- sd(x)
sy <- sd(y)

nx <- length(x)
ny <- length(y)

s_delta <- sqrt((sx^2/nx) + (sy^2/ny))

t <- ( x_bar - y_bar ) / s_delta
t
## [1] -2.64566
t.test(x,y)$statistic
##        t 
## -2.64566
